<br>
Look at the thread <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showMessage?topicID=3744.topic">Mages of TM Unite!</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->  It shows that other group styles are possible, and can even be made popular.  Or my effort to promote <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showMessage?topicID=3824.topic">The UnHoly Trinity</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->.<br>
<br>
There is no reason to accept the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> &quot;classic&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> group as the be-all and end-all of groups.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Razamatazz Pizzazz</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
