<br>
More boring personal monk experience:<br>
<br>
I wander over to The Grey.  Already have all the decent drops there, at 60 I just want some AA points out of the shissar there.  I solo along, takes 10-40% life to kill any given mob depending on adds and dependability of Instil Doubt, etc.<br>
<br>
Mage wanders in, shouts LFG a few times.  I'm in antisocial soloing mode, I pay no attention to anyone LFG regardless of class.  Finally mage shouts &quot;LFG or port outta here&quot;.  Catches my attention, I call her over to the temple, and we go at it.<br>
<br>
So what's &quot;wrong&quot; with this situation?  According to you guys, the mage is 100% worthless here.  Pet doesn't tank, mage doesn't tank, rogue would outdamage, shaman would be safer, pet might train, only buff is a DS, mage can't heal, mages suck, rogues rock, life's a bitch, blah blah blah blah...<br>
<br>
Well neither of us gave a S#(*, she fired up a DS and a water pet and we killed mobs approximately twice as fast.  I never ran out of bandages, what's that worth?  Pretty much as a monk who is always at 24.8 stone while AC reduction point is 25 stone.  Rockfiend add? /shrug, dead in less than a minute and I doubt I outdamaged the mage, those have ridiculous AC.<br>
<br>
Anyway, my point...we had a good time, got a little XP out of it.  Could I have gotten more solo?  /shrug.  Would I have gotten more fearkiting with a bard?  /shrug.  Would I have gotten more if I was a rogue with two other rogues and a cleric and chanter and warrior and we had a mob vending machine that spat out 1k HP level 90 mobs that hit for 10 and had a very low AC?  Yeah, I admit, probably.  But then again, how often do you find those.<br>
<br>
 - Reyn<br>
<br>
That pet is quite large.<br>
