<br>
Finding a group isn't always easy.. people do tend to be biased about mages until they learn about them.. And yes, if you get a good rep (have your pet offtank two adds in velks when your chanter goes LD, and let the recognition flow) then people aren't grouping with a stereotypical mage, they're grouping with the &quot;exception.&quot;<br>
<br>
I'm gonna avoid every sociological implication that raises, those are why we keep raz around  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
The point being, if you sit lfg and complain to everyone how hard it is to find groups, <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u> people start believing you.</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> <br>
<br>
Your best bet in finding a group, the &quot;main&quot; reason for this thread, is to get a guildy group.   Guildies will be more willing to group with you, simply because they know you, and know what you're capable of.. However, I don't wanna step on any toes by bringing the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  social </i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> aspects of the game up again. <br>
<br>
Evidently mages problems are solely based upon coding, and as a class are a bug leftover from the beta days. That being the case, don't worry, they'll remove the &quot;mage class&quot; bug in a future patch.<br>
<br>
